Lecture 3
=============
I read the slites and watch the viedos on the Youtube.

Learn that there are many attributes for files. And uid and gid control file permissions.

Learn how ls(1) can display most of the information from the struct stat. stat(1) gets us the rest in a more flexible way.

Before class:
-------------
Only root and the owner of a file can change its permissions.

Only root can change the owner of a file, but the owner may change the group ownership of a file.
